'''EpiBone''' is a [[biomedical engineering]] company that is developing technology to create bone tissue from a patient's [[mesenchymal stem cells]] ''in vitro'' for use in [[bone grafts]]. The company was founded by [[Nina Tandon]].<ref>{{cite book |last1=Murphy |first1=Sean V. |last2=Atala |first2=Anthony |title=Regenerative Medicine Technology: On-a-Chip Applications for Disease Modeling, Drug Discovery and Personalized Medicine |date=2016 |publisher=CRC Press |isbn=9781498711920 |page=407 |url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=TqqdDQAAQBAJ&pg=PA407 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = This Woman's Revolutionary Startup Could Change 900,000 Surgeries A Year|url = http://www.businessinsider.com/nina-tandon-of-epibone-grows-bones-from-stem-cells-2014-11|website = Business Insider|accessdate = 2015-10-20}}</ref>
