{{unreferenced|date=November 2011}} [[File:Gilbert Weston plants potatoes with a horse drawn planter - NARA - 285503.tif|thumb|A horse-drawn potato planter]] [[File:Kartoffellegemaschine Teller.jpg|thumb|Half-automatic potato planter]] [[File:Amflora Pflanzung 2010 Grimme.jpg|thumb|A modern 8-row trailed potato planter]] A '''potato planter''' is a [[farm implement]] for [[sowing]] seed [[potato]]es.
A manual planter is sometimes called a '''bell planter''', which may have two farm hands sitting on the back whilst taking potatoes from a hopper. The length between potatoes is tolled by a [[Bell (instrument)|bell]], at the sound of which potatoes are thrown down tubes.
An automatic planter is hitched behind a [[Farm_tractor#Farm_tractor_design.2C_power_and_transmission|farm tractor]] with a [[three-point hitch|three-point linkage]] and [[towing|towed]]. Cups lift seed potatoes from a hopper and drop them in tubes, planting up to eight drills at a time.
